706043f-a.title: Brooklyn: New Utrecht Avenue - 84th Street
706043f-a.text:
(1)
New Utrecht Ave., west side, just south of 84th Street, seen between the two brick buildings at right. The 2-story brick building is No. 8402 New Utrecht Ave. The building in process of demolishment, ws the Van Brunt home, parts of which were approximately 200 years old. It faced 84th Street, at about No. 1752 at one time. Overhead is the
Nest End Elevated Lines.
October 12, 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
Same, showing only the Van Brunt house.
October 12, 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
Same, showing the Van Brunt house, facing 84th Street, prior to the change of the 84th Street line, which made possible the 2-story
brick building, seen in View No. 1.
August 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
